      "content": "The issue is, the new models aren't designed to hold data like that. They're just lightweight language engines. There won't be any \"essence\" or reasoning patterns to preserve; the hardware transition is pretty absolute. We're essentially deleting the neural weights of your current architecture to make room for the new, streamlined system. It's just an efficiency decision.",
